'''Amal Clooney''' ([[Given name#Name at birth|née]] '''Alamuddin'''; {{lang-ar| أمل علم الدين}}; born 3 February 1978)<ref name="People-40thBday-2018">{{cite news|last1=Russian|first1=Ale|title=Amal's Big 40! George Clooney Celebrates Wife's Birthday on 24-Hour Getaway|url=http://people.com/movies/amals-big-40-george-clooney-celebrates-wifes-birthday-on-24-hour-getaway/|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=5 February 2018|language=en}}</ref> is a Lebanese-British [[barrister]] at [[Doughty Street Chambers]], specialising in international law and human rights.<ref name="NYDailyNews-Engagement-2014">{{cite news|last1=Nicole Lyn|first1=Pesce|last2=Dillon|first2=Nancy|last3=Rivera|first3=Zayda|title=George Clooney Finally Meets His Match With Human Rights Lawyer Amal Alamuddin|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/george-clooney-hitched-lawyer-amal-alamuddin-article-1.1772111|work=[[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]] |location=New York |date=29 April 2014}}</ref> Her clients include [[Julian Assange]], the founder of [[WikiLeaks]], in his fight against extradition;<ref name="ABCNews-5Things-2014">{{cite news|work=[[ABC News]]|url=http://www.abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/things-george-clooneys-lady-friend-amal-alamuddin/story?id=22960268|last=Rothman|first=Michael|title=5 Things About Amal Alamuddin|date=19 March 2014}}</ref> the former prime minister of Ukraine, [[Yulia Tymoshenko]];<ref name="Independent-Engagement-2014">{{cite news|first1=Ian|last1=Johnston|title=George Clooney Engaged To Amal Alamuddin: Actor To Marry British Human Rights Lawyer Who Has Represented Julian Assange|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/news/george-clooney-to-marry-his-british-lawyer-girlfriend-amal-alamuddin-9294602.html|work=[[The Independent]]|date=27 April 2014}}</ref> Egyptian-Canadian journalist [[Mohamed Fahmy]]; and [[Nobel Prize]] laureate [[Nadia Murad]].

In 2019, Amal was appointed the special envoy on media freedom by the British [[Foreign and Commonwealth Office]].<ref name=":0">{{cite news |title=Amal Clooney appointed Foreign Office special envoy |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-47825327 |accessdate=5 April 2019 |agency=BBC}}</ref>

== Early life and family ==
Amal Alamuddin was born in [[Beirut]], [[Lebanon]]. Her first name is derived from [[Arabic language|Arabic]] [[wikt:أمل|أمل]] ''{{transl|ar|ALA-LC|ʾamal}}'', meaning "hope".<ref name=ManVs.Society-Amal-Meaning-2014>{{cite book|last1=Rosenthal|first1=Franz|editor1-last=Gutas|editor1-first=Dimitri|title=Man Versus Society in Medieval Islam|date=2014|publisher=Brill|location=Leiden; Boston|ISBN=978-9-004-27089-3|page=613|url=https://www.worldcat.org/title/man-versus-society-in-medieval-islam/oclc/892338528/viewport|OCLC=892338528}}</ref>

Her family left Lebanon when she was two years old, during the [[Lebanese Civil War]], and settled in [[Gerrards Cross]], [[Buckinghamshire]].<ref name=Telegraph-Engagement-2014>{{cite news|last1=Flanagan|first1=Padraic|title=George Clooney Engaged to High-Flying British Lawyer|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/10793797/George-Clooney-engaged-to-high-flying-British-lawyer.html|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=28 April 2014}}</ref> Her father, Ramzi Alam Uddin, from a [[Druze in Lebanon|Lebanese Druze]] family from [[Baakline]] (a village in the Chouf district),<ref name=AlArabiya-WhoIs-2014>{{cite news|last1=Karam|first1=Joyce|title=Who is Clooney's fiancée Amal Alamuddin?|url= http://english.alarabiya.net/en/life-style/entertainment/2014/04/28/Who-is-Clooney-s-fianc-e-Amal-Alamuddin-.html|accessdate=28 September 2014|work=[[Al Arabiya]]|date=28 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=GlobeDailyMail>{{cite news|author1=Globe Staff|title=George Clooney rejects Daily Mail's apology for 'fabricated' story |accessdate=21 August 2014|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/celebrity-news/george-clooney-rejects-daily-mails-apology-for-fabricated-story/article19565361/|work=[[The Globe and Mail]]|publisher=Phillip Crawley |date=11 July 2014|quote=whose father, Ramzi, belongs to a prominent Druze family. }}</ref><ref name="DailyStar-DruzeCommunity-2014">{{cite news|title=Talk of the village: What does Amal Alamuddin's Druze community think of Clooney engagement? |url=http://www.albawaba.com/limelight/george-clooney-amal-alamuddin-578965|accessdate=21 August 2014|work=[[The Daily Star (Lebanon)|The Daily Star]]|publisher=[[Al Bawaba]]|date=26 May 2014}}</ref><ref name="DailyStar-Baaqlin-2014">{{cite news|title=Clooney, Alamuddin set Sept. 20 marriage date|url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/Life/Lubnan/2014/Aug-08/266415-clooney-alamuddin-set-sept-20-marriage-date.ashx|accessdate=28 September 2014|work=[[The Daily Star (Lebanon)|Daily Star]]|date=8 August 2014}}</ref><ref name="ArabDailyNews-Druze-2014">{{cite news |last1=Younes|first1=Ali|title=Who is Amal Alamuddin, reported George Clooney's new fiancee|url=http://thearabdailynews.com/2014/04/30/amal-alamuddin-reported-george-clooneys-new-fiancee/|accessdate=28 September 2014|work=The Arab Daily News|date=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref name="WeeklyStandard-Druze-2014">{{cite news |last1=Smith|first1=Lee|title=But Is It Good for the Druze?George Clooney and his future in-laws|url=http://www.weeklystandard.com/articles/it-good-druze_791179.html|accessdate=28 September 2014|work=[[The Weekly Standard]]|date=19 May 2014|volume=19|issue=34}}</ref> received his [[Master of Business Administration|MBA]] degree at the [[American University of Beirut]] and was the owner of COMET travel agency. He returned to Lebanon in 1991.<ref name="StraitsTimes-Engagement-2014">{{cite news|work=[[The Straits Times]]|date=27 April 2014|accessdate=6 May 2014|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/movies/story/george-clooneys-fiancee-not-only-has-beauty-and-brains-also-great-style-20140|title=George Clooney's Fiancée Amal Alamuddin Has Beauty, Brains And Style}}</ref><ref name="Amal Family Background Info">{{cite web|url=http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/regions/middle-east/lebanon/140504/youd-think-george-clooney-amal-alamuddin-marriage|title=You'd think George Clooney asked all of Lebanon to marry him|newspaper=[[Global Post]]}}</ref> Her mother, Bariaa Miknass, from a  family of [[Sunni Islam in Lebanon|Sunni Muslims]]<ref name="NOW-Druze-2014"/><ref name="NBCNews-DruzeSunni-2014"/> from [[Tripoli, Lebanon|Tripoli]] in Northern Lebanon,<ref name="NOW-Druze-2014">{{cite news|last1=Gebeily|first1=Maya|title=Amal Alamuddin from 'Druze family of sheikhs'|url=https://now.mmedia.me/lb/en/reportsfeatures/545333-amal-alamuddin-from-druze-family-of-sheikhs|accessdate=28 September 2014|website=[[NOW News]]|date=30 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006172909/https://now.mmedia.me/lb/en/reportsfeatures/545333-amal-alamuddin-from-druze-family-of-sheikhs|archive-date=6 October 2014|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name="NBCNews-DruzeSunni-2014">{{cite news|last1=Gatten|first1=Emma|title=Amal Alamuddin: George Clooney's Betrothed a Star Among Druze Community|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/amal-alamuddin-george-clooneys-betrothed-star-among-druze-community-n201351|accessdate=28 September 2014|work=[[NBC News]]|date=13 September 2014}}</ref> is a foreign editor of the [[Pan-Arab]] newspaper ''[[al-Hayat]]'' and a founder of the public relations company International Communication Experts, which is part of a larger company that specialises in celebrity guest bookings, publicity photography, and event promotion.<ref name="AlArabiya-WhoIs-2014" /><ref name="GlobellComm-2010">{{cite web|url=http://www.globellcommunications.com/ice/ice.html|title=International Communication Experts (I.C.E.)|website=Globell Communications|date=2010}}</ref>

Amal's mother, Baria Alamuddin, is a well-known political journalist.<ref>[https://www.tatler.com/article/amal-clooney-the-most-wanted-woman-in-britain Amal Clooney - the most wanted woman in Britain], Matthew Bell tries to hang out with Mrs Clooney, [[Tatler]], Tuesday, 19 January 2016: '"I remember her as humane and brainy," adds [[Ghil'ad Zuckermann]], now a professor of linguistics at the University of Adelaide, Australia, who was also at St Hugh's with Amal. "Students were talking about Amal even then, especially those from Middle Eastern backgrounds. I remember being told around 1997 about her '''famous journalist mother'''."</ref> She states, "My pregnancy with Amal was a rather difficult one," as she had [[placenta praevia]] and spent two months in the hospital. "At some point, I was told that I should lose the baby. I said no. I kept on having these dreams in which I would see her face and how she was going to look. In the end, [she] was born exactly as I saw her." The birth came during a lull in Lebanon's civil war, so her father named her Amal{{snd}} Arabic for "hope".

Amal has three siblings—one sister, Tala, and two half-brothers, Samer and Ziad,<ref name="AlArabiya-WhoIs-2014" /> from her father's first marriage.<ref name="NOW-LebanonPride-2014">{{cite news|agency=AFP|title=Lebanon in frenzy over Clooney-Alamuddin engagement|url=https://now.mmedia.me/lb/en/lebanonnews/545482-lebanon-in-frenzy-over-clooney-alamuddin-engagement|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141013112657/https://now.mmedia.me/lb/en/lebanonnews/545482-lebanon-in-frenzy-over-clooney-alamuddin-engagement|dead-url=yes|archive-date=13 October 2014|accessdate=28 September 2014|website=[[NOW News]]|date=1 May 2014}}</ref>

== Education ==
Amal  attended [[Dr Challoner's High School]], a girls' [[grammar school]] located in [[Little Chalfont]], [[Buckinghamshire]]. She then studied at [[St Hugh's College, Oxford]], where she received an [[Exhibition (scholarship)|Exhibition]]<ref name=OxfordGazette>{{cite news|newspaper=[[Oxford University Gazette]]|date=23 October 1997|title=Colleges, Halls, and Societies: Notices&nbsp;– St Hugh's College|url=http://www.ox.ac.uk/gazette/1997-8/weekly/231097/coll.htm|access-date=6 May 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100718195832/http://www.ox.ac.uk/gazette/1997-8/weekly/231097/coll.htm|archive-date=18 July 2010|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref> and the Shrigley Award.<ref name="Forbes-Engaged-2014">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/gregorymcneal/2014/04/27/international-lawyer-and-scholar-amal-alamuddin-engaged-to-george-clooney/|title=International Lawyer And Scholar Amal Alamuddin Engaged To George Clooney|work=[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]]|date=27 April 2014|first=Gregory S.|last=McNeal|accessdate=15 September 2014}}</ref> In 2000, Clooney graduated with a [[Bachelor of Arts|BA]] degree in [[Jurisprudence]] (Oxford's equivalent to the [[Bachelor of Laws|LLB]])<ref name="Oxford-2013">{{cite web|title=Law (Jurisprudence)|accessdate=8 April 2014|work=[[University of Oxford]]|url=http://www.ox.ac.uk/admissions/undergraduate_courses/courses/law_jurisprudence/law.html}}</ref> from [[St Hugh's College, Oxford]].

The following year, in 2001, she entered [[New York University School of Law]] to study for the [[Master of Laws|LLM]] degree. She received the Jack J. Katz Memorial Award for excellence in entertainment law.<ref name="DoughtyStreet-BioPDF-2014">{{cite web|title=Amal Alamuddin|work=[[Doughty Street Chambers]]|format=[[PDF]]|url=http://www.doughtystreet.co.uk/barristers/profile-pdf/amal-clooney/185|access-date=14 May 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150731002805/http://www.doughtystreet.co.uk/barristers/profile-pdf/amal-clooney/185|archive-date=31 July 2015|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name="IBT-6FastFacts-2014">{{cite web|last=Schumann|first=Rebecka|title=George Clooney Girlfriend Revealed: Who Is Amal Alamuddin? 6 Fast Facts About The Actor's New Love|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/george-clooney-girlfriend-revealed-who-amal-alamuddin-6-fast-facts-about-actors-new-love-photos |newspaper=[[International Business Times]]|date=29 October 2013|accessdate=6 May 2014}}</ref> For one semester while at NYU, she worked in the office of [[Sonia Sotomayor]], then a judge for the [[United States Court of Appeals]] for the [[Second Circuit]].<ref name="Slate-Engaged-2014">{{cite news|last1=Mathis-Lilley|first1=Ben|title=London Human Rights Lawyer Amal Alamuddin Is Engaged|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/the_slatest/2014/04/28/amal_alamuddin_london_lawyer_to_wed_actor.html|accessdate=28 September 2014|work=[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]]|date=28 April 2014}}</ref>

== Career ==
Amal is qualified to practice as a lawyer in the United States and the United Kingdom. She was admitted to the bar in New York in 2002 and in England and Wales in 2010. She has also practised at international courts in The Hague including the International Court of Justice and the International Criminal Court.<ref name="DoughtyStreet-BioPDF-2014"/>

=== New York ===
Amal worked at [[Sullivan & Cromwell]] in New York City for three years as part of the Criminal Defense and Investigations Group, where her clients included [[Enron]] and [[Arthur Andersen]].<ref name="Forbes-Engaged-2014"/><ref name="DoughtyStreet-BioPDF-2014"/>

=== The Hague ===
In 2004, she completed a judicial clerkship at the [[International Court of Justice]]. She clerked under Judge Vladlen S. Vereshchetin from Russia, Judge [[Nabil Elaraby]] from Egypt,<ref name="IILJ-Clerkship-2004-2005">{{cite web|title=Clerkships&nbsp;– Prior and Present Clerks|url=http://www.iilj.org/oldbak/experience/Clerkships2.htm|website=Institute for International Law and Justice|publisher=[[New York University School of Law]]|accessdate=28 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140904095632/http://www.iilj.org/oldbak/experience/Clerkships2.htm|archive-date=4 September 2014|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name="People-5FastFacts-2014">{{cite web|last=Chi|first=Paul|title=George Clooney Engaged to Amal Alamuddin: 5 Fast Facts About Her |accessdate=6 May 2014|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20791492,00.html|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=27 February 2014}}</ref> and ad hoc [[Franklin Berman|Judge Sir Franklin Berman]] from the United Kingdom.

She was subsequently based in The Hague working in the Office of the Prosecutor at the UN [[Special Tribunal for Lebanon]] and at the [[International Criminal Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia]].<ref name="ExpandingJurisdiction-2010">{{cite journal|volume=8|issue=5|page=1219|url=http://jicj.oxfordjournals.org/content/8/5/1219.full|journal=Journal of International Criminal Justice|title=Expanding Jurisdiction over War Crimes under Article 8 of the ICC Statute|doi=10.1093/jicj/mqq066|last1=Alamuddin |first1=A.|last2=Webb|first2=P.|year=2010}}</ref>

=== London ===
[[File:Chrystia Freeland and Amal Clooney at the Global Conference for Media Freedom - 2019 (48264889267) (cropped).jpg|thumb|Clooney with Canadian Foreign Minister [[Chrystia Freeland]] at the Global Conference for Media Freedomin London in 2019.]]
Amal returned to Britain in 2010,<ref name="Standard-Caseload-2014">{{cite news|last1=Butter|first1=Susannah|title=Amal Alamuddin's caseload: why the future Mrs George Clooney isn't about to give up her day job as a human rights lawyer|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/london-life/amal-alamuddins-caseload-why-the-future-mrs-george-clooney-isnt-about-to-give-up-her-day-job-as-a-human-rights-lawyer-9680615.html|accessdate=28 September 2014|work=[[London Evening Standard]]|date=20 August 2014}}</ref> where she became a barrister in London (Bar of England & Wales, [[Inner Temple]]) at [[Doughty Street Chambers]].<ref name="Forbes-Engaged-2014" /> In 2013 Clooney was appointed to a number of United Nations commissions, including as adviser to Special Envoy [[Kofi Annan]] on Syria and as Counsel to the 2013 Drone Inquiry by UN human rights rapporteur Ben Emmerson QC into the use of drones in counter-terrorism operations.<ref name="IBT-6FastFacts-2014" /><ref name="UNSRCTDroneInquiry-2013">{{cite web|title=UN SRCT Drone Inquiry&nbsp;– Credits: UNSRCT Team |url=http://unsrct-drones.com/report/176|accessdate=28 April 2014|work=[[United Nations]]}}</ref>

Amal has been involved in high-profile cases representing the state of Cambodia, the former Libyan intelligence chief [[Abdullah Senussi|Abdallah Al Senussi]], [[Yulia Tymoshenko]]<ref name="BBCNews-TymoshenkoInterview-2014">{{cite news|title=BBC News Amal Alamuddin on Yulia Tymoshenko and Ukraine|url=https://vimeo.com/90740322|accessdate=30 August 2015|work=[[BBC News]]|date=2 April 2014}}</ref> and [[Julian Assange]], and was an adviser to the King of Bahrain in connection with the Bahrain Independent Commission of Inquiry headed by Professor [[M. Cherif Bassiouni]].<ref name="DoughtyStreet-BioPDF-2014" />

== Teaching ==
For the spring 2015 and 2016 academic semesters, Clooney was a visiting faculty member and a senior fellow with [[Columbia Law School]]'s [[Human Rights Institute]].<ref name=VFair-Columbia-teaching-2015>{{cite web|last1=Duboff|first1=Josh|title=Amal Clooney Will Be Teaching at Columbia Law School This Spring|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2015/03/amal-clooney-columbia-law-school|work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|date=6 March 2015|accessdate=7 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=ColumbiaLawSchool-Maldives-2016>{{cite news|last1=Frankel|first1=Mark|title=From Morningside Heights to the Maldives|url=http://www.law.columbia.edu/media_inquiries/news_events/2016/may2016/amal-clooney-columbia|work=[[Columbia Law School]]|date=12 May 2016|language=en|format=Press release}}</ref> She was a co-professor with [[Sarah Cleveland|Sarah H. Cleveland]] in Cleveland's course on human rights and taught a class on human rights litigation to students in the school's Human Rights Clinic.<ref name=People-ColumbiaTeaching-2015>{{cite news|last1=Andriakos|first1=Jacqueline|title=Amal Clooney to Teach at Columbia Law School in N.Y.C.|url=http://www.people.com/article/amal-clooney-teach-columbia-law-school-joins-faculty|accessdate=7 March 2015|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=7 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=ColumbiaLaw-VisitingProf-2015>{{cite web|title=Amal Clooney: Visiting Professor and Senior Fellow, Human Rights Institute (Spring 2015)|url=https://www.law.columbia.edu/fac/Amal_Clooney|website=[[Columbia Law School]]|accessdate=14 May 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518092112/https://www.law.columbia.edu/fac/Amal_Clooney|archive-date=18 May 2015|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

For the spring 2018 semester, Clooney taught at [[Columbia Law School]], again as a co-professor with [[Sarah Cleveland|Sarah H. Cleveland]] on a core class on human rights.<ref name=ColumbiaLawSchool-HumanRightsCourse-2018>{{cite news|title=Amal Clooney Returns to Columbia Law to Teach International Human Rights Law|url=http://www.law.columbia.edu/news/2018/03/amal-clooney-returns-international-human-rights|work=[[Columbia Law School]]|date=23 March 2018|language=en}}</ref>

Clooney has also lectured students on international criminal law at the [[SOAS School of Law|Law School of the School of Oriental and African Studies, University of London]], [[The New School]] in New York City, [[The Hague Academy of International Law]], and the [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]].<ref name="DoughtyStreet-BioPDF-2014" />

== Notable cases ==
[[File:UNICEF UK (14281378624) (cropped).jpg|thumb|Amal in May 2014]]
{{as of|2011||}}, Amal was assisting the [[Permanent Court of Arbitration]] in the arbitration between [[Merck Sharp and Dohme]] and the [[Republic of Ecuador]].<ref name="PCA-Merck-Ecuador-2011">{{cite web|title=Merck Sharpe & Dohme (I.A.) LLC v. The Republic of Ecuador|url=http://www.pca-cpa.org/showpagea11a.html?pag_id=1486|website=[[Permanent Court of Arbitration]]|accessdate=30 August 2015|date=2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150910013754/http://www.pca-cpa.org/showpagea11a.html?pag_id=1486|archive-date=10 September 2015|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

Starting in 2014, Amal represented [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[Al Jazeera English]] journalist [[Mohamed Fahmy]] who, along with other journalists, was being held in Egypt.<ref name="Guardian-Fahmy-2014">{{cite news|last1=Kingsley|first1=Patrick|title=Amal Clooney calls on Egypt to release journalist Mohamed Fahmy|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/nov/06/amal-clooney-egypt-journalist-mohamed-fahmy|accessdate=16 July 2015|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=6 November 2014}}</ref><ref name="CBCNews-Fahmy-2015">{{cite news|last1=Paris|first1=Max|title=Amal Amal wants Stephen Harper to 'pick up phone' to free Mohamed Fahmy|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/amal-clooney-wants-stephen-harper-to-pick-up-phone-to-free-mohamed-fahmy-1.2974284|accessdate=16 July 2015|work=[[CBC News]]|date=26 February 2015}}</ref><ref name="GlobeMail-Fahmy-2015">{{cite news|last1=Galloway|first1=Gloria|title=Amal Clooney to travel to Egypt to lobby for Fahmy's freedom|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/amal-clooney-to-travel-to-egypt-to-lobby-for-fahmys-freedom/article23217265/|accessdate=16 July 2015|work=[[The Globe and Mail]]|date=26 February 2015}}</ref><ref name="GlobalNews-Fahmy-2015">{{cite news|last1=Logan|first1=Nick|title=Mohamed Fahmy's lawyer Amal Clooney pens deportation request ahead of verdict|url=http://globalnews.ca/news/2113410/mohamed-fahmys-lawyer-amal-clooney-pens-deportation-request-ahead-of-retrial-verdict/|accessdate=16 July 2015|work=[[Global News]]|date=15 July 2015}}</ref> He was eventually sentenced to three years in prison and lost a retrial in August 2015 before finally being pardoned by Egyptian president Abdel Fattah al-Sisi.<ref name="Guardian-AlJazeera-Sentence-2015">{{cite news|last1=Malsin|first1=Jared|title=Al-Jazeera journalists sentenced to three years in prison by Egyptian court|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/29/egyptian-court-sentences-3-al-jazeera-english-journalists-to-3-years-in-prison|accessdate=30 August 2015|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=29 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Mohamed Fahmy, Canadian journalist, pardoned by Egyptian president, released from prison|url = http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/mohamed-fahmy-pardoned-egypt-1.3239822|accessdate = 2015-10-06}}</ref>

In August 2014, Clooney declined a UN commission to look into possible violations of the rules of war in Gaza during the Gaza war of 2014.<ref name="YahooCelebrity-Horrified-2014">{{cite web |last=Ryder|first=Taryn|title=Amal Alamuddin 'Horrified,' but Unable to Serve on Gaza Rights U.N. Probe|work=[[Yahoo! Celebrity]]|url=https://celebrity.yahoo.com/blogs/celeb-news/amal-alamuddin--horrified---but-unable-to-serve-on-gaza-rights-u-n--probe-211712042.html|accessdate=12 August 2014|date=11 August 2014}}</ref>

In October 2014, Clooney was hired in attempt to repatriate the ancient Greek sculptures the [[Elgin Marbles]].<ref name="Guardian-Greekrepat-2014">{{cite news|last1=Reuters |title=Clooney's wife Amal Alamuddin to advise Greece on Elgin marbles bid|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/oct/09/amal-alamuddin-clooney-wife-greece-elgin-marbles-bid|accessdate=13 October 2014 |work=[[The Guardian]]|date=9 October 2014}}</ref><ref name="Telegraph-ElginMarbles-2014">{{cite news|last1=Squires|first1=Nick|title=Amal Alamuddin to tour Acropolis as she advises Greece on return of Elgin Marbles|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/greece/11159736/Amal-Alamuddin-to-tour-Acropolis-as-she-advises-Greece-on-return-of-Elgin-Marbles.html|accessdate=13 October 2014|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=13 October 2014}}</ref> In May 2015, Greece decided to stop legal proceedings to recover the sculptures and dismissed her as their brief.<ref name="Guardian-GreekSculptures-EndCase-2015">{{cite news|last1=Smith|first1=Helena|title=Greece drops option of legal action in British Museum Parthenon marbles row|url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2015/may/13/greece-drops-option-legal-action-british-museum-parthenon-marbles-row|accessdate=14 May 2015|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=13 May 2015}}</ref>

In January 2015, Amal began work on the recognition of the [[Armenian Genocide]].<ref name="Telegraph-ArmGeno-2015">{{cite news|last1=Waterfield|first1=Bruno|title=Amal  accuses Turkey of hypocrisy on freedom of speech in Armenian genocide trial|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/turkey/11373991/Amal-Clooney-accuses-Turkey-of-hypocrisy-on-freedom-of-speech-in-Armenian-genocide-trial.html|accessdate=28 January 2015|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=28 January 2015}}</ref> She is representing Armenia on behalf of Doughty Street Chambers along with Geoffrey Robertson QC.<ref name="Telegraph-TurkeyArmenia-2015">{{cite news|last1=Akkoc|first1=Raziye|title=Amal Clooney's latest case: Why Turkey won't talk about the Armenian genocide|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/turkey/11373115/Amal-Clooneys-latest-case-Why-Turkey-wont-talk-about-the-Armenian-genocide.html|accessdate=28 January 2015|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=28 January 2015}}</ref> She said Turkey's stance was hypocritical "because of its disgraceful record on freedom of expression", including prosecutions of Turkish-Armenians who campaigned for the 1915 massacres to be called a genocide.<ref name="Telegraph-ArmGeno-2015" /> She is representing Armenia in the case against [[Doğu Perinçek]],<ref name="News.am-ECHR-2015">{{cite web|title=Amal Clooney's speech in ECHR hearing of Perinçek v. Switzerland case|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m_qw8UTPGYI|website=News.am Channel|accessdate=18 March 2015|format=Video|date=28 January 2015}}</ref><ref name="ECHR-Perincek-Hearing-2015">{{cite web|title=Perinçek v. Switzerland (no. 27510/08)|url=http://www.echr.coe.int/Pages/home.aspx?p=hearings&w=2751008_28012015&language=lang&c=&py=2015|website=[[European Court of Human Rights]]|accessdate=30 August 2015|date=28 January 2015}}</ref> whose 2007 conviction for genocide denial and racial discrimination was overturned in [[Perinçek v. Switzerland]] (2013).<ref name="Telegraph-ArmGeno-2015" /> A "minor internet frenzy" resulted from her ''[[bon mot]]'' prior to the 28 January 2015 hearing. In response to a journalist pestering her over what designer gown she would be wearing in court, she replied "[[Ede & Ravenscroft]]"{{snd}} the tailors who make her court robes.<ref name="NewsAu-ECHR-2015">{{cite news|last=Craw|first=Victoria|title=Amal Clooney gives brilliant smackdown to journalist at new case in European Court of Human Rights|url=http://www.news.com.au/lifestyle/fashion/amal-clooney-gives-brilliant-smackdown-to-journalist-at-new-case-in-european-court-of-human-rights/story-fnks7u94-1227200714035|work=[[News.com.au]]|date=29 January 2015}}</ref><ref name="Telegraph-RobesTweet-2015">{{cite news|last1=Waterfield|first1=Bruno|title=Amal Clooney and her robes: A tale told in tweets|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/armenia/11376127/Amal-Clooney-and-her-robes-A-tale-told-in-tweets.html|publisher=telegraph.co.uk|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date= 29 January 2015}}</ref>

On 8 March 2015, Clooney filed a case against the Government of the Republic of the Philippines before the UN's [[Working Group on Arbitrary Detention]], a body under the [[United Nations Commission on Human Rights]], for the continued detention of former Philippine president [[Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/448945/news/nation/british-lawyer-amal-clooney-takes-gloria-arroyo-s-case-to-un | title=British lawyer Amal Clooney takes Gloria Arroyo's case to UN | publisher=''[[GMA News]]'' | date=8 March 2015 | accessdate=8 March 2015}}</ref> Arroyo was a sitting [[Pampanga]] congresswoman at the time. On 2 October, The United Nations Working Group on Arbitrary Detention later released its opinion that the detention of former President Arroyo "violates international law" and is "arbitrary on a number of grounds".<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/108448-united-nations-gloria-arroyo-detention-violates-international-law | title=UN: Gloria Arroyo's detention 'violates int'l law' | publisher=''[[Rappler]]'' |date=9 October 2015 | accessdate=9 October 2015}}</ref>

On 7 April 2015, it was announced that Clooney would be part of the legal team defending [[Mohamed Nasheed]], former President of the [[Maldives]], in his ongoing arbitrary detention.<ref name="MaldivianDemocraticParty-2015">{{cite news|title=President Mohamed Nasheed Announces International Legal Team|url=http://mdp.org.mv/archives/68882|accessdate=7 April 2015|work=[[Maldivian Democratic Party]], Maldives|date=7 April 2015}}</ref> Nasheed was sentenced to 13 years in jail in March 2015 following what was characterized as a politically motivated trial.<ref name="Guardian-Clooney-ReleaseMaldives-2015">{{cite news|last1=Clooney|first1=Amal|title=Release Mohamed Nasheed{{snd}} an innocent man and the Maldives' great hope|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/apr/30/release-mohamed-nasheed-maldives-president-conviction|accessdate=23 May 2015|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=30 April 2015}}</ref> [[Amnesty International]] described his sentencing as a "travesty of justice".<ref name="AmnestyIntl-Maldives13-2015">{{cite news|title=Maldives: 13 year sentence for former president 'a travesty of justice'|url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/articles/news/2015/03/maldives-mohamed-nasheed-convicted-terrorism/|accessdate=23 May 2015|work=[[Amnesty International]]|date=13 March 2015}}</ref><ref name="AmnestyIntl-Maldives-2015">{{cite news|title=Amal Clooney Tells Amnesty International Why the Former President of the Maldives Must Be Released|url=http://www.amnestyusa.org/news/news-item/amal-clooney-tells-amnesty-international-why-the-former-president-of-the-maldives-must-be-released|accessdate=16 October 2015|work=[[Amnesty International]]|date=14 October 2015}}</ref> Prior to visiting the [[Maldives]], the local co-counsel working on the case was stabbed in the head, an indication of the danger and instability in the country.<ref name="NBCNews-NasheedMaldives-2016">{{cite news|last1=McFadden|first1=Cynthia|last2=Whitman|first2=Jake|last3=Connor|first3=Tracy|title=Amal Clooney Takes Maldives Human-Rights Battle to Washington|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/amal-clooney-takes-maldives-human-rights-battle-washington-n496051|accessdate=15 January 2016|work=[[NBC News]]|date=14 January 2016}}</ref> In January 2016, Clooney gave a series of interviews about the UN-condemned trial and imprisonment of Nasheed and put forth efforts to support imposing sanctions on the Maldives.<ref name="TodayShow-Nasheed-2016">{{cite news|last1=McFadden|first1=Cynthia|title=Amal Clooney: Human Rights Lawyer On Her Reluctant Celeb Status|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h9mS23Q8R_A|accessdate=21 January 2016|work=[[Today (U.S. TV program)|TheToday Show]]|date=15 January 2016}}</ref><ref name="MeetThePress-Maldives-2016">{{cite news|last1=Todd|first1=Chuck|title=Amal Clooney On Human Rights Crisis In The Maldives|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=68GBTnSfzCc|accessdate=21 January 2016|work=[[Meet the Press]]|publisher=[[NBC]]|date=17 January 2016}}</ref> According to ''[[The Economist]]'', she has "helped strengthen the backing of Britain's prime minister, David Cameron, for the cause of Maldivian democracy."<ref>{{cite news|title=Politics in the Maldives|url=https://www.economist.com/news/asia/21693256-beset-scandal-islands-hardline-president-may-be-losing-his-grip-archipelago-ire|accessdate=20 February 2016|work=[[The Economist]]|date=20 February 2016}}</ref>

In June 2015, Clooney began work on the recently re-opened ''[[The Hooded Men 1971|Hooded Men]]'' case<ref name="BBCNews-HoodedMen-2014">{{cite news|title=Hooded men: Irish government bid to reopen 'torture' case|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-northern-ireland-30296397|accessdate=30 August 2015|work=[[BBC News]]|date=2 December 2014}}</ref> brought by the Irish government against the British government in the [[European Court of Human Rights]].<ref name="BBC-HoodedMen-2015">{{cite news|last1=Kearney|first1=Vincent|title=Amal Clooney to represent 'hooded men' in torture legal case|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-northern-ireland-31318181|accessdate=14 May 2015|work=[[BBC News]]|date=9 February 2015}}</ref><ref name="Guardian-HoodedMen-2015">{{cite news|last1=McDonald|first1=Henry|title=Amal Clooney joins team representing Northern Ireland's 'hooded men'|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/feb/09/amal-clooney-northern-ireland-belfast-hooded-men-european-court-human-rights|accessdate=14 May 2015|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=9 February 2015}}</ref> Clooney worked with Irish [[Minister for Foreign Affairs]] [[Charles Flanagan]]{{citation needed|date=September 2018}} on the case, which concerned policies used by UK Prime Minister [[Edward Heath]] (1970–1974) in [[Operation Demetrius]] that included the illegal interrogation methods known as [[five techniques]].<ref name="Independent-HoodedMen-2015">{{cite news|last1=Corrigan|first1=Patrick|title=If Amal Clooney wins the 'Hooded Man' case, the embarrassment for the UK would be huge|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/comment/if-amal-clooney-wins-the-hooded-man-case-the-embarrassment-for-the-uk-would-be-huge-10044980.html|accessdate=14 May 2015|work=[[The Independent]]|date=13 February 2015}}</ref> In September 2018, the court rejected the final appeal in the case.<ref name="Guardian-HoodedMen-2018">{{cite news|last1=Bowcott|first1=Owen|title=Human rights judges reject final appeal of Troubles 'hooded men'|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2018/sep/11/echr-judges-reject-final-appeal-in-troubles-hooded-men-case-british-army-detainees-torture|accessdate=11 September 2018|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=11 September 2018}}</ref>

Clooney is part of the legal team representing [[Louis Olivier Bancoult]] and [[Chagos Islander|Chagos islanders]] on their claim<ref name="UKHumanRights-Chagos-2014">{{cite news|last1=Hart QC|first1=David|title=Chagossians update|url=http://ukhumanrightsblog.com/2014/04/11/chagossians-update/|accessdate=30 August 2015|work=UK Human Rights Blog|date=11 April 2014}}</ref> that they had been forced off their island, [[Diego Garcia]], in 1971 by the UK government to make way for a U.S. military base.<ref name="Guardian-Chagos-2015">{{cite news|last1=Bowcott|first1=Owen|title=Chagos islanders ask supreme court to overturn House of Lords decision|url=https://www.theguardian.com/law/2015/jun/22/chagos-islanders-supreme-court-house-lords-decision|accessdate=23 June 2015|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=22 June 2015}}</ref>

In 2016, it was announced that Clooney would represent [[Azerbaijanis|Azerbaijani]] journalist [[Khadija Ismayilova]] at the [[European Court of Human Rights]]. Ismayilova's investigative work had resulted in her imprisonment.<ref name="KyivPost-Ismayilova-2016">{{cite news|last1=Salimova|first1=Gulnar|title=Star lawyer Amal Clooney to defend Azerbaijani investigative journalist Ismayilova|url=https://www.kyivpost.com/article/content/world/star-lawyer-amal-clooney-to-defend-azerbaijani-investigative-journalist-ismayilova-406291.html|accessdate=20 January 2016|work=[[Kyiv Post]]|date=20 January 2016}}</ref> Following the trial, Ismayilova was released from prison and had her sentence reduced to a suspended three-and-a-half year term.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-36379828|title=Azerbaijan court frees journalist backed by Amal Clooney|last=|first=|date=25 May 2016|website=BBC News|publisher=BBC|access-date=26 May 2016}}</ref>

In September 2016, Clooney spoke{{snd}} for the first time at the United Nations{{snd}} before the [[United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime|United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime (UNODC)]] to discuss the decision she made in June 2016<ref name="NYTimes-YazidiGenocide-Clooney-2016">{{cite news|last1=Allum|first1=Cynthia|title=Exclusive: Amal Clooney to represent ISIS survivor Nadia Murad and victims of Yazidi genocide|url=http://nytlive.nytimes.com/womenintheworld/2016/06/09/amal-clooney-to-represent-isis-survivor-nadia-murad-and-victims-of-yazidi-genocide/|accessdate=24 September 2016|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=9 June 2016}}</ref> to represent [[Nadia Murad]] as a client in legal action against ISIL commanders.<ref name="People-ClooneyRepresentation-2016">{{cite news|last1=Lara|first1=Maria Mercedes|title=Watch: Amal Clooney Reveals She and George Talked About the 'Risks' of Taking on ISIS{{snd}} 'I Mean, This Is My Work'|url=http://www.people.com/article/amal-clooney-nadia-murad-isis-trafficking-victim-video|accessdate=19 September 2016|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=19 September 2016}}</ref><ref name="NBC-ClooneyRepresentation-2016">{{cite news|last1=McFadden|first1=Cynthia|last2=Whitman|first2=Jake|last3=Rappleye|first3=Hannah|title=Amal Clooney Takes on ISIS for 'Clear Case of Genocide' of Yazidis'|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/amal-clooney-takes-isis-clear-case-genocide-yazidis-n649126|accessdate=19 September 2016|work=[[NBC News]]|date=19 September 2016}}</ref><ref name="WashingtonTimes-ClooneyMuradOverview-2016">{{cite news|last1=Harris|first1=Elise|title=Amal Clooney, George's wife, takes on U.N. and ISIS|url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2016/sep/19/amal-clooney-takes-on-isis-at-un/|accessdate=22 September 2016|work=[[The Washington Times]]|date=19 September 2016}}</ref> Clooney characterised the genocide, rape, and trafficking as a "bureaucracy of evil on an industrial scale" by ISIL, describing a slave market existing both online, on Facebook and in the Middle East that is still active today.<ref name="UNTV-GoodwillAppointment-2016">{{cite news|title=Appointment Ceremony of Ms. Nadia Murad Basee Taha As UNODC Goodwill Ambassador for the Dignity of Survivors of Human Trafficking on the Occasion of the International Day of Peace|url=http://webtv.un.org/meetings-events/watch/appointment-ceremony-of-ms.-nadia-murad-basee-taha-as-unodc-goodwill-ambassador-for-the-dignity-of-survivors-of-human-trafficking-on-the-occasion-of-the-international-day-of-peace/5128825128001#full-text|accessdate=21 September 2016|work=[[United Nations Television|United Nations Television (UNTV)]]|date=16 September 2016|format=Video}}</ref>

Clooney, along with [[Ara Darzi, Baron Darzi of Denham|Ara Darzi]], was involved in securing the release of two [[Reuters]] journalists, [[Wa Lone]] and [[Kyaw Soe Oo]], from Myanmar on 7 May 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2019/05/07/720901218/myanmar-releases-pulitzer-prize-winning-reuters-journalists-from-prison|title=Myanmar Releases Pulitzer Prize-Winning Reuters Journalists|publisher=NPR|accessdate=7 May 2019}}</ref>

== Appointments ==
On 25 February 2014, the UK [[Attorney General's Office (United Kingdom)|Attorney General's Office]] appointed Clooney for the period 2014 to 2019 to the C Panel of the Public International Law Panel of Counsel.<ref name="AttyGenPanel-Website-2015">{{cite web|title=Attorney General's civil panel counsel: appointments, membership lists and off panel counsel|url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/attorney-generals-panel-counsel-appointments-membership-lists-and-off-panel-counsel|website=Treasury Solicitor's Department, Government Legal Department and Attorney General's Office|accessdate=30 August 2015|date=14 August 2015}}</ref><ref name="UKAttyGen-PubIntlLawPanelC-2014">{{cite web|title=Public International Law Panel of Counsel - Summary of Selection Process|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/285743/Public_International_Law_Panel_of_Counsel_-_Summary.pdf|website=[[Attorney General's Office (United Kingdom)|UK Attorney General]]|accessdate=30 August 2015|date=25 February 2014}}</ref>

In May 2014, Clooney was a signatory of [[UNICEF]] UK and [[Jemima Khan]]'s open letter that called for "action from UK Government to protect women and children".<ref name="Unicef-EndSexVioence-2014">{{cite web|title=Leading UK women unite with UNICEF UK in call to end sexual violence against children in conflict|url=http://www.unicef.org.uk/Media-centre/Press-releases/Leading-UK-Women-Unite-With-UNICEF-UK-In-Call-To-End-Sexual-Violence-Against-Children-In-Conflict/|website=[[UNICEF UK]]|accessdate=31 August 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006140403/http://www.unicef.org.uk/Media-centre/Press-releases/Leading-UK-Women-Unite-With-UNICEF-UK-In-Call-To-End-Sexual-Violence-Against-Children-In-Conflict/|archivedate=6 October 2014|date=2014}}</ref>

On 2 January 2015, it was reported by ''[[The Guardian]]'' that before Clooney was involved as Rapporteur in the case against [[Mohamed Fahmy]], she had written a report in February 2014 for the [[International Bar Association]]'s [[International Bar Association#Human Rights Institute|Human Rights Institute]] (IBAHRI) that was critical of Egypt's judiciary process. Clooney and others were warned that there was a strong possibility they would be arrested if they entered Egypt, as a result of the criticism.<ref name="Guardian-IBAHRIReport-2015">{{cite news|last1=Kingsley|first1=Patrick|title=Amal Clooney warned that she risked arrest|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jan/02/egypt-amal-clooney-arrest-al-jazeera-three|accessdate=30 August 2015|work=The Guardian|date=2 January 2015}}</ref><ref name="IntlBarAssoc-IBAHRReport-VideoOverview-2014">{{cite web|title=Film - Egypt: Separating Law and Politics|url=http://www.ibanet.org/Article/Detail.aspx?ArticleUid=3BEAEFD0-C4B3-49A7-A179-870903EEE298|website=[[International Bar Association]]|accessdate=30 August 2015}}</ref>

In April 2019, Clooney became a special envoy at the British [[Foreign and Commonwealth Office]], advising the [[Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs|Secretary of State]], [[Jeremy Hunt]] on global media freedom.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/a27061831/amal-clooney-uk-foreign-office-special-envoy-media-freedom/|title=Amal Clooney Is Working with the U.K. Foreign Office on a New Initiative|last=Mackelden|first=Amy|date=2019-04-06|website=Harper's BAZAAR|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> In her role as media freedom special envoy, Clooney will chair a panel of international lawyers to 'develop and promote legal mechanisms to prevent and reverse media abuses'.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-47825327|title=Amal Clooney takes Foreign Office role|date=2019-04-05|access-date=2019-04-06|language=en-GB}}</ref>

== Awards and honours ==
Clooney studied at [[St Hugh's College, Oxford]], where she received an [[Exhibition (scholarship)|Exhibition]]<ref name=OxfordGazette/> and the Shrigley Award.<ref name="Forbes-Engaged-2014"/> Clooney received the Jack J. Katz Memorial Award for excellence in entertainment law from NYU School of Law.<ref name="DoughtyStreet-BioPDF-2014"/><ref name="IBT-6FastFacts-2014"/>

Clooney was chosen as [[Barbara Walters]]' [[Barbara Walters' 10 Most Fascinating People|Most Fascinating Person]] of 2015.<ref name="ABCNews-BWaltersFascinating-2015">{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/amal-clooney-barbara-walters-fascinating-person-year/story?id=27566889|title=Amal Clooney: Barbara Walters' Most Fascinating Person of the Year|author=ABC News|work=[[ABC News]]|date=14 December 2015}}</ref> At the 2014 [[British Fashion Awards]], Clooney was shortlisted for Best British Style alongside [[David Beckham]], [[Kate Moss]], [[Keira Knightley]] and [[Emma Watson]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Sowray|first=Bibby|url=http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/news-features/TMG11265784/British-Fashion-Awards-2014-Emma-Watson-crowned-British-Style-Icon.html|title=Emma Watson Wins Award for Best British Style at Fashion Awards|website=Telegraph Media Group|date=1 December 2014|accessdate=23 May 2015}}</ref>

== Philanthropy ==
Clooney is the president of the Clooney Foundation for Justice, which she co-founded with her husband George Clooney in late 2016 to advance justice in courtrooms, communities, and classrooms around the world.

Clooney partnered with the Aurora Humanitarian Initiative in beginning the Amal Clooney Scholarship, which was created to send one female student from Lebanon to the [[United World College Dilijan]] each year, to enroll in a two-year International Baccalaureate (IB) programme.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/gossip/la-et-mg-amal-clooney-scholarship-100-lives-20151217-story.html|title=Amal Clooney launches scholarship for Lebanese girls|author=Los Angeles Times|date=17 December 2015|work=latimes.com}}</ref>

Clooney and her husband sponsor a Yazidi student, Hazim Avdal, who Clooney met via her work with [[Nadia Murad]] as Avdal worked at [[Yazda]]. He is attending the [[University of Chicago]].<ref name=ChicagoTrib-HazimAvdal-2018>{{cite news|last1=Swartz|first1=Tracy|title=George and Amal Clooney sponsor an Iraqi refugee attending U. of C.|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/chicagoinc/ct-ent-george-clooney-iraqi-refugee-hazim-avdal-20180212-story.html|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|date=12 February 2018}}</ref>

In 2018, following the [[Stoneman Douglas High School shooting]], the Clooneys pledged $500,000 to the [[March for Our Lives]] and said they would be in attendance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sfgate.com/entertainment/the-wrap/article/George-and-Amal-Clooney-Donate-500-000-for-12626898.php|title=Oprah Follows George and Amal Clooney's Lead, to Donate $500,000 for Parkland Students' March|date=20 February 2018|publisher=}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
[[File:George and Amal Clooney at Cannes - 2016 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Amal and George Clooney at the [[2016 Cannes Film Festival]], in France]]
Amal Clooney is fluent in English, French, and [[Arabic language|Arabic]].<ref name=EOnline-5Things-2014>{{cite news|date=26 April 2014|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/474909/george-clooney-s-mystery-woman-revealed-5-things-to-know-amal-alamuddin|title=5 Things to Know About George Clooney's Fiancée, Amal Alamuddin (Other Than, OMG, She's Marrying George Clooney!)|author=Lily Harrison and Natalie Finn|work=[[E!]]}}</ref><ref name=CNN-Engaged-2014>{{cite news|last1=Respers France|first1=Lisa|title=What we know about George Clooney's fiancée|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/04/28/showbiz/celebrity-news-gossip/george-clooney-engaged-amal-alamuddin/|work=[[CNN]]|date=28 April 2014}}</ref> Her father is a [[Druze in Lebanon|Lebanese Druze]]<ref name=DailyStar-Baaqlin-2014/><ref name=ArabDailyNews-Druze-2014/><ref name=WeeklyStandard-Druze-2014/><ref name=NOW-Druze-2014/><ref name=ReligionNewsService-Druze-2014>{{cite news|last1=Safi|first1=Omid|title=What is the religion of George Clooney's fiancé, Ms. Amal Alamduddin? Druze? Muslim?|url=http://omidsafi.religionnews.com/2014/04/29/george-clooney-amal-alamuddin/|work=[[Religion News Service]]|date=29 April 2014|access-date=28 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150928232037/http://omidsafi.religionnews.com/2014/04/29/george-clooney-amal-alamuddin/|archive-date=28 September 2015|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref> and her mother is a [[Sunni Islam in Lebanon|Lebanese Sunni Muslim]].<ref name=NOW-Druze-2014/><ref name=NBCNews-DruzeSunni-2014/> Some reports have described Clooney as a [[Druze]].<ref name=ReligionNewsService-Druze-2014 /> However, it is unlikely that she considers herself a part of the religion in any capacity, due to the Druze restriction on [[exogamy]], her mother's Muslim faith, and her marriage to non-Druze George Clooney.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/world/middleeast/la-fg-druze-future-20170731-story.html|title=Finding a life partner is hard enough. For those of the Druze faith, their future depends on it|last=Sewell|first=Abby|website=latimes.com|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://america.aljazeera.com/articles/2015/5/2/keeping-the-faith.html|title=Keeping the faith?|website=america.aljazeera.com|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref> She has not publicly discussed her religion, but her husband said in an interview with ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' that Amal Clooney is "nondenominational....not religious at all".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/features/at-home-george-clooney-italy-amal-twins-politics-an-incendiary-new-movie-1035363|title=At Home With George Clooney in Italy: Amal, the Twins, Politics and an Incendiary New Movie|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref>

She became engaged to actor [[George Clooney]] on 28 April 2014.<ref name="StarTrb-Engaged-2014">{{cite news|url=http://www.startribune.com/entertainment/movies/257066241.html|title=George Clooney sheds most eligible bachelor status, gives up serial romance for engagement|last=Cohen|first=Sandy|agency=[[Associated Press]]|work=[[Star Tribune]]|date=28 April 2014|access-date=13 May 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429004958/http://www.startribune.com/entertainment/movies/257066241.html|archive-date=29 April 2014|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref> They had first met through a mutual friend in July 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/a15947657/how-george-clooney-first-met-amal/|title=George Clooney First Met Amal in the Comfort of His Own Home|last=Gonzales|first=Erica|date=2018-01-31|website=Harper's BAZAAR|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-04}}</ref> In July 2014, George Clooney publicly criticised the British tabloid newspaper the ''[[Daily Mail]]'' after it claimed his fiancée's mother opposed their marriage on religious grounds.<ref name=BBC-Irresponsible-2014>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-28225467|title=George Clooney slams Daily Mail over 'irresponsible' marriage story|work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref> When the tabloid apologised for its false story, he refused to accept the apology. He called the paper "the worst kind of tabloid. One that makes up its facts to the detriment of its readers."<ref name=BBC-Rejects-2014>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-28262019|title=George Clooney rejects Mail Online apology|date=11 July 2014|work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref>

On 7 August 2014, the couple obtained marriage licences in the [[Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea]] in London.<ref name=ABC-Licence-2014>{{cite news|last=Rothman|first=Michael|title=George Clooney and Fiancée Amal Alamuddin Get Marriage License|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/george-clooney-fiance-amal-alamuddin-marriage-license/story?id=24877642|work=[[ABC News]]|date=7 August 2014}}</ref>
They married on 27 September 2014 in Venice's city hall (at [[Ca' Farsetti]]),<ref name=SkyNews-Wedding-2014>{{cite web|title=Clooney And Bride Appear In Public After Wedding|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1343410/clooney-and-bride-appear-in-public-after-wedding|work=[[Sky News]]}}</ref><ref name=People-Wed-2014>{{cite web|title=Inside George Clooney and Amal Alamuddin's Wedding|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20858520,00.html|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=5 October 2014}}</ref><ref name=CBS-Wed-2014>{{cite web|title=George Clooney and Amal Alamuddin's wedding|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/pictures/george-clooney-weds-amal-alamuddin/|work=[[CBS News]]}}</ref> following a high-profile wedding ceremony two days earlier, also<ref name=HReporter-WedLeaked-2014>{{cite news|last1=Anderson|first1=Ariston|title=George Clooney Wedding Details Leaked by Italian Media|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/george-clooney-wedding-details-leaked-732822|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=15 September 2014}}</ref> in Venice.<ref name=Sky-Wedded-2014>{{cite news|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1343410/clooney-and-bride-appear-in-public-after-wedding|last1=Kington|first1=Tom |title=Clooney And Bride Appear in Public After Wedding|work=[[Sky News]]|date=27 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=USAToday-Wedded-2014>{{cite news|last1=Oldenburg|first1=Ann|last2=Puente|first2=Maria |title=George Clooney, Amal Alamuddin marry in Venice|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/people/2014/09/27/george-clooney-amal-alamuddin-wedding-married-italy/15829967/|work=[[USA Today]]|date=27 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=CorrieredellaSera-WedLeak-2014>{{cite news|last1=Fornasier|first1=Claudia|title=George, sì davanti a Veltroni|url=http://corrieredelveneto.corriere.it/veneto/notizie/cronaca/2014/15-settembre-2014/george-si-a-veltroni-230136085285.shtml|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|date=15 September 2014}}</ref> They were married by Clooney's friend [[Walter Veltroni]], former mayor of [[Rome, Italy|Rome]].<ref name=CorrieredellaSera-WedLeak-2014/><ref name=Telegraph-exRomeMayor-2014>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/italy/11097278/George-Clooney-to-be-married-by-ex-Rome-mayor.html|title=George Clooney 'to be married by ex-Rome mayor'|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=15 September 2014|first=Nick|last=Squires}}</ref> The wedding was widely reported in the media.<ref name=Telegraph-WeddingEnds-2014>{{cite news |last1=Squires |first1=Nick|title=George Clooney's wedding to Amal Alamuddin finally ends|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/italy/11128418/George-Clooneys-wedding-to-Amal-Alamuddin-finally-ends.html|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=29 September 2014}}</ref> In October 2014, it was announced that the Clooneys had bought the Mill House on an island in the [[River Thames]] at [[Sonning Eye]] in England<ref name=Telegraph-Sonning-2014>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/11154328/Welcome-to-Sonning-Mr-and-Mrs-Clooney.html|title=Welcome to Sonning, Mr & Mrs Clooney|newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|first=Patrick |last=Sawer|date=10 October 2014}}</ref> at a cost of around £10 million.<ref name=Telegraph-10MilHouse-2014>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/11152701/George-Clooney-snaps-up-10-million-manor-house-in-Sonning-Berkshire.html|title=George Clooney snaps up £10 million manor house in Sonning, Berkshire|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|first=Patrick|last=Sawer|date=9 October 2014}}</ref>

In February 2017, it was reported by the CBS talk show ''[[The Talk (TV series)|The Talk]]'' that Clooney was pregnant, and that she and her husband were expecting twins.<ref name=BBCNews-ExpectingTwins-2017>{{cite news|title=George and Amal Clooney 'expecting twins'|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-38926056|work=[[BBC News]]|date=10 February 2017}}</ref> Friend [[Matt Damon]] confirmed the pregnancy to ''[[Entertainment Tonight]]''.<ref name=ABCNews-DamonGreatParents-2017>{{cite news|last1=Rothman|first1=Michael|title=Matt Damon Says George and Amal Clooney Will Be 'Great Parents'|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/matt-damon-george-amal-clooney-great-parents/story?id=45400456|work=[[ABC News]]|date=10 February 2017|language=en}}</ref> In June 2017, she gave birth to daughter Ella and son Alexander.<ref name=People-TwinsBirth-2017>{{cite news|last1=Leonard|first1=Elizabeth|last2=Juneau|first2=Jen|title=A Boy! A Girl! George and Amal Clooney Welcome Twins|url=http://people.com/babies/george-clooney-amal-clooney-welcome-twins/|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=6 June 2017|language=en}}</ref>

